
Blockmatic is a highly configurable Tetris clone written in C99.
It requires SDL2, SDL2_TTF and SDL2_image to be linked against.

Available options:

	--help
 		list available options

	--background-file file.{png,jpg,bmp}
 		the path to a background image
 		default: rgb(205,205,205)

	--block-file file.{png,jpg,bmp}
 		the path to the blocks image
 		default: 'simple.png'

	--block-size number
 		the standard size for blocks (width == height, used when computing the window's size)
 		default: 24 px, min: 1

	--blocks-per-col number
 		the number of blocks per column (used when computing the window's height)
 		default: 20, min: 8

	--blocks-per-row number
 		the number of blocks per row (used when computing the window's width)
 		default: 14, min: 8

	--decrease number
 		the percentage of duration (ms) decrease
 		default: 10%, min: 0, max: 99

	--delay number
 		the number of seconds before duration (ms) is decreased by decrease (%)
 		default: 60%, min: 1, max: 86400

	--duration number
 		the number of milliseconds to wait before moving down a tetri
 		default: 2000%, min: 100, max: 10000

	--font-file file.{otf,ttf}
 		the path to the font file to be used to display various informations
 		default: 'Cantarell-Bold.otf'

	--font-size number
 		the size of the font, pause text will be twice this size
 		default: 18

	--nohints
 		if set, no hints will be displayed (hints == time remaining until moving down)
 		default: hints allowed

	--nokeyrepeat
 		if set, key repeat will be disabled
 		default: key repeat enabled

	--nopreview
 		if set, the next tetrimino can't be previewed
 		default: preview enabled

	--pausemsg string
 		the message to be displayed when the game is paused
 		default: 'PAUSE'

	--restart
 		if set, when the game is over, a new game is started
 		default: no restart

	--rows number
 		the number of rows to be randomly filled with blocks at the beginning
 		default: 0, min: 0, max: 20 or the user-defined number of blocks per column

	--threshold number
 		the number of rows to be completed before duration (ms) is decreased by decrease (%)
 		default: 10%, min: 1, max: 1000000

	--usedelay
 		to decide if duration (ms) must be decreased after delay (s)
 		default: use threshold

	--window-icon file.{png,jpg,bmp}
 		the path to the window's icon file
 		default: 'icon.png'

	--window-title string
 		the window's title
 		default: 'Blockmatic'

Runtime control keys:

	n
		new game

	escape
		leave game

	p
		pause game

	left
		move left

	right
		move right

	up
		counter-clockwise rotation

	down
		clockwise rotation

	shift + down
		move down

	space
		drop tetri

	?
		delete last row (cheat mode)


